The Obama administration asks United States District Court for the Central District of California judge Virginia A. Phillips to stay her ruling in Log Cabin Republicans v. United States of America that the Don't Ask, Don't Tell policy is unconstitutional while it appeals the decision. (Reuters)Guinea sets November 7 as the new date for the presidential run-off. (Reuters) (Al Jazeera)The Supreme Court in Burma hears an appeal from lawyers of Aung San Suu Kyi against her house arrest. (Bangkok Post) (BBC)